oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Nashville medal issued to World War I veterans
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This Nashville Medal was issued to John William Cato. It consists of a bronze bar bearing "1918", a red/white/blue vertical striped ribbon suspension, and a bronze medal featuring Liberty seated at the center of a large star, superimposed upon a ring having the words "FOR/DEMOCRACY/LIBERTY/AND/JUSTICE" arranged between the arms of the star.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
